cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning models for reading comprehension, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also focuses on the speed of the models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of convolutional neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often uses similar architectures. Finally, the paper mentions dilated convolutional units, which are a relatively new development in deep learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
